name: Dallas Stars
summary: The Edmonton Oilers and Dallas Stars are facing off in the Western Conference Finals. Game 2 of the series took place on May 31st, with the Stars defeating the Oilers 3-1. The game was tied going into the third period, but Mason Marchment broke the stalemate with a goal to give the Stars the lead. The Stars held on to their lead and won the game, tying the series at 1-1. The Oilers and Stars will face off again in Game 3 on June 2nd.

name: Lexi Thompson
summary: Lexi Thompson, a prominent golfer with 15 LPGA Tour victories, has announced her retirement from full-time competition at the age of 29. The announcement was made on various news platforms, including Forbes, The Associated Press, LPGA, NBC Sports, CBS Sports, Golf.com, GolfDigest.com, Sports Illustrated, and Golfweek. Thompson, known for her contributions to the U.S. Women's Open and her advocacy for small businesses and kindness, will step away from professional golf at the end of the 2024 season. Her decision to retire follows a successful career that included 11 LPGA Tour wins and numerous top-10 finishes in major championships.

name: Rafah
summary: Multiple news sources have reported on an Israeli airstrike on a camp near Rafah, Gaza, that resulted in significant casualties. Reuters and The Associated Press cited Palestinian officials who claimed 21 and 35 people were killed, respectively, while NPR stated that 45 Palestinians died in an encampment for displaced people. The American Jewish Committee provided context on Rafah's importance to Hamas and emphasized protecting its civilian population. CNN reported on the global condemnation of the strike, which prompted outrage from world leaders, as noted by NBC News. Al Jazeera reported that Israeli airstrikes also targeted Rafah's two hospitals, exacerbating the danger for residents. POLITICO revealed that Biden officials were in discussions with an EU group to assist in reopening the Rafah crossing. The Associated Press highlighted the International Court of Justice's order for Israel to halt its offensive in Gaza, although Israel expressed reluctance to comply.
